					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/sh85118979" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Pentateuch scroll. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="3r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer Torah </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר תורה</title>
							<note>
								<p>The scroll begins with Gen. 48:7. The following portions are due to other hands: Ex. 29:38-34:1; Lev. 6:6-8:16; Deut. 16:18-21:2, 25:1-28:12, 32:25-34:12. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>46 membranes, 188 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>523</height>
										<width>2522</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>46 membranes, with header/wrapper (620mm). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Surface occasionally dry, dark and crazed. </p>
									<p>A few delaminations. </p>
									<p>Old repairs, including linen supports on verso, with glue stains. </p>
									<p>Edge damage. Water marks in part. </p>
									<p>Stained, with some degraded leather tearing. </p>
									<p>Ink offset to verso from damp, flaking in places.
</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="188" ruledLines="48" writtenLines="48">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and stitching. </p>
									<p>188 columns in total, three to six columns per membrane. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on the letters שעטנזגץ. </p>
									<p>Special arrangement of lines of the Song of Moses, Ex. 15. The first דרש of Lev. 10:16 is written at the middle of the line. Puncta extraordinaria placed only on most of the words fixed by the masorah. </p>
									<p>Majuscular and minuscular letters occur. </p>
									<p>The inverted letter nun is placed before and after Num. 10:35-36. Some of the shaper of the letter ח is arched. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
